The paper presents a framework for solving computer vision problems with event cameras, which are commonly used in robotics and autonomous systems. The paper focuses on motion, depth, and optical flow estimation, which are all subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions that the proposed method implicitly handles data association, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). The method involves maximizing an objective function, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions that the proposed method produces motion-corrected images, which is a common task in neural networks (cs.NE).
